HEADWORD: Dispope
<hw>Dis*pope"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To refuse to
consider as pope; to depose from the popedom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One whom they <qex>dispoped</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disporous</ent>⟦br⟧
